{
  "$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/abbaye/WpfHexEditorIDE/master/schemas/whfmt/v2.0.json",
  "diffMode": "binary",
  "formatName": "Excel Workbook (Legacy)",
  "formatId": "XLS",
  "version": "1.13",
  "extensions": [
    ".xls",
    ".xlt",
    ".xlm"
  ],
  "description": "Microsoft Excel 97-2003 workbook (.xls) stored in the OLE2 Compound File Binary (CFB) container. Shares the 8-byte CFB magic (D0CF11E0A1B11AE1) with .doc and .ppt. Excel-specific identification: root entry CLSID {00020820-0000-0000-C000-000000000046} or the 'Workbook' stream (Excel 97+) or 'Book' stream (Excel 5.0/95) in the CFB directory. The 'Workbook' stream contains BIFF8 (Binary Interchange File Format 8) records: each record has a 2-byte type (uint16 LE) + 2-byte length (uint16 LE) + variable-length data. Key BIFF8 records: 0x0009=BOF (Beginning of File — version discriminator), 0x0085=BoundSheet8 (sheet names), 0x003C=CONTINUE, 0x00E0=XF (Cell formatting), 0x02BD=SharedStr (shared strings table).",
  "category": "Documents",
  "author": "WPFHexaEditor Team",
  "preferredEditor": "hex-editor",
  "references": {
    "specifications": [
      "[MS-CFB] Compound File Binary Format — Microsoft Open Specifications",
      "[MS-XLS] Excel Binary File Format (.xls) BIFF8 v10.0 — Microsoft Open Specifications",
      "OLE2 Compound Document File Format"
    ],
    "WebLinks": [
      "https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/openspecs/office_file_formats/ms-xls/",
      "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Excel",
      "https://www.loc.gov/preservation/digital/formats/fdd/fdd000510.shtml"
    ]
  },
  "detection": {
    "signature": "D0CF11E0A1B11AE1",
    "offset": 0,
    "required": true,
    "Strength": "Strong",
    "EntropyHint": {
      "min": 3.5,
      "max": 7.0
    },
    "validation": {
      "minFileSize": 512,
      "note": "OLE2/CFB magic. Disambiguate as .xls by: (1) root entry CLSID {00020820-...} or (2) 'Workbook'/'Book' stream in directory. First BIFF8 record in Workbook stream is BOF (type=0x0809, subtype 0x0500=workbook, 0x0010=worksheet, 0x0020=chart)."
    }
  },
  "variables": {
    "ole2Signature": "",
    "minorVersion": 0,
    "majorVersion": 0,
    "byteOrder": 0,
    "sectorSizeExp": 0,
    "fatSectorCount": 0,
    "firstDirSector": 0,
    "miniStreamCutoff": 0,
    "isXLS97": false
  },
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "signature",
      "name": "OLE2/CFB Magic",
      "offset": 0,
      "length": 8,
      "color": "#FF6B6B",
      "opacity": 0.45,
      "description": "OLE2 Compound File Binary magic: D0 CF 11 E0 A1 B1 1A E1. Shared by all legacy Office formats. Excel-specific content is in the 'Workbook' or 'Book' stream within the CFB directory.",
      "storeAs": "ole2Signature",
      "valueType": "ascii"
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "Minor Version",
      "offset": 24,
      "length": 2,
      "color": "#4ECDC4",
      "opacity": 0.3,
      "description": "CFB minor version (LE uint16). Must be 0x003E (62) for all valid OLE2/CFB files.",
      "storeAs": "minorVersion",
      "valueType": "uint16",
      "endianness": "little",
      "valueMap": {
        "62": "0x003E — standard (all valid OLE2/CFB files)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "Major Version",
      "offset": 26,
      "length": 2,
      "color": "#95E1D3",
      "opacity": 0.3,
      "description": "CFB major version (LE uint16). 3 = 512-byte sectors (Office 97-2003), 4 = 4096-byte sectors.",
      "storeAs": "majorVersion",
      "valueType": "uint16",
      "endianness": "little",
      "valueMap": {
        "3": "Version 3 — 512-byte sectors (standard)",
        "4": "Version 4 — 4096-byte sectors (large files)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "Byte Order",
      "offset": 28,
      "length": 2,
      "color": "#FFE66D",
      "opacity": 0.25,
      "description": "Byte order mark: must be 0xFFFE (little-endian). OLE2/CFB is always little-endian.",
      "storeAs": "byteOrder",
      "valueType": "uint16",
      "endianness": "little",
      "valueMap": {
        "65534": "0xFFFE — little-endian (required)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "Sector Size Exponent",
      "offset": 30,
      "length": 2,
      "color": "#C7CEEA",
      "opacity": 0.25,
      "description": "Power-of-2 sector size: 9 = 512 bytes, 12 = 4096 bytes.",
      "storeAs": "sectorSizeExp",
      "valueType": "uint16",
      "endianness": "little",
      "valueMap": {
        "9": "512-byte sectors (standard)",
        "12": "4096-byte sectors"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "FAT Sector Count",
      "offset": 44,
      "length": 4,
      "color": "#B8B8FF",
      "opacity": 0.25,
      "description": "Number of FAT sectors in the container. FAT maps sector chain for all streams.",
      "storeAs": "fatSectorCount",
      "valueType": "uint32",
      "endianness": "little"
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "First Directory Sector",
      "offset": 48,
      "length": 4,
      "color": "#FFA07A",
      "opacity": 0.3,
      "description": "Sector index of the first directory stream sector. Byte offset = (firstDirSector+1) × sectorSize.",
      "storeAs": "firstDirSector",
      "valueType": "uint32",
      "endianness": "little"
    },
    {
      "type": "field",
      "name": "Mini Stream Cutoff",
      "offset": 56,
      "length": 4,
      "color": "#C7CEEA",
      "opacity": 0.2,
      "description": "Streams smaller than this size (default 4096 bytes) use the mini FAT stream. Standard is 0x1000.",
      "storeAs": "miniStreamCutoff",
      "valueType": "uint32",
      "endianness": "little"
    },
    {
      "type": "computeFromVariables",
      "name": "Is XLS 97+ Format",
      "expression": "calc:majorVersion == 3 && minorVersion == 62",
      "storeAs": "isXLS97",
      "description": "True for standard OLE2 v3 container — the expected Excel 97-2003 format"
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "CFB Major Version",
      "variable": "majorVersion",
      "description": "OLE2 CFB major version"
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "First Directory Sector",
      "variable": "firstDirSector",
      "description": "Sector index of CFB directory"
    },
    {
      "type": "metadata",
      "name": "Is XLS 97 Format",
      "variable": "isXLS97",
      "description": "True when standard OLE2 v3 CFB container"
    }
  ],
  "assertions": [
    {
      "name": "CFB minor version valid",
      "expression": "minorVersion == 62",
      "severity": "error",
      "message": "CFB minor version must be 0x003E (62) — not a valid OLE2 container"
    },
    {
      "name": "CFB major version valid",
      "expression": "majorVersion == 3 || majorVersion == 4",
      "severity": "error",
      "message": "CFB major version must be 3 or 4"
    },
    {
      "name": "Byte order little-endian",
      "expression": "byteOrder == 65534",
      "severity": "error",
      "message": "OLE2 byte order must be 0xFFFE"
    }
  ],
  "navigation": {
    "bookmarks": [
      {
        "name": "CFB Header",
        "offset": 0,
        "icon": "",
        "color": "#FF6B6B"
      },
      {
        "name": "Directory Stream",
        "offsetVar": "firstDirSector",
        "icon": "",
        "color": "#4ECDC4"
      },
      {
        "name": "File Start",
        "offset": 0,
        "description": "Beginning of file / magic bytes"
      }
    ]
  },
  "inspector": {
    "badge": "majorVersion",
    "primaryField": "firstDirSector",
    "showQualityScore": true,
    "groups": [
      {
        "title": "CFB Container",
        "icon": "",
        "fields": [
          "ole2Signature",
          "majorVersion",
          "minorVersion",
          "byteOrder"
        ]
      },
      {
        "title": "Sector Layout",
        "icon": "",
        "fields": [
          "sectorSizeExp",
          "fatSectorCount",
          "firstDirSector",
          "miniStreamCutoff"
        ]
      },
      {
        "title": "Excel Format",
        "icon": "",
        "fields": [
          "isXLS97"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "displayFields": [
      "formatName",
      "version",
      "description"
    ],
    "valueMaps": {},
    "tooltips": {}
  },
  "exportTemplates": [
    {
      "name": "OLE2 Header (JSON)",
      "format": "json",
      "fields": [
        "majorVersion",
        "minorVersion",
        "byteOrder",
        "sectorSizeExp",
        "fatSectorCount",
        "firstDirSector",
        "isXLS97"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Python OLE2 check",
      "format": "python-bytes",
      "fields": [
        "ole2Signature",
        "majorVersion",
        "minorVersion"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "forensic": {
    "category": "document",
    "riskLevel": "high",
    "suspiciousPatterns": [
      {
        "name": "VBA macro stream",
        "condition": "majorVersion == 3 || majorVersion == 4",
        "severity": "info",
        "description": "Excel .xls files can embed VBA macros in a 'VBA' stream. Excel macros have been the primary delivery vehicle for financial malware (Emotet, TrickBot, Dridex, Ursnif downloaders). Use olevba to extract and analyze."
      },
      {
        "name": "Invalid CFB byte order",
        "condition": "byteOrder != 65534",
        "severity": "error",
        "description": "OLE2 byte order is not 0xFFFE — file is corrupt or non-conformant."
      }
    ],
    "knownExploitVectors": [
      "CVE-2017-8570: .xls with OLE packager embedding .sct (scriptlet) file — MSOffice RCE",
      "CVE-2012-0158: MSCOMCTL.OCX ListView exploit triggered in Excel via embedded control",
      "XLM macro (Excel 4.0 macros) in 'Macro' sheet — commonly abused in modern malware (2020-2022) to evade VBA detection",
      "DDEAUTO formula in cells triggering system command execution",
      "CVE-2018-0802: Equation Editor OLE object in Excel cells"
    ],
    "notes": [
      "OLE2 compound binary; contains multiple streams that may embed macros.",
      "VBA macro streams (VBA/ directory) are a common malware vector.",
      "Summary information streams expose author, company, and revision metadata."
    ]
  },
  "aiHints": [
    "Legacy .xls = OLE2 CFB container. Excel data in 'Workbook' (Excel 97+) or 'Book' (Excel 5/95) stream. BIFF8 record format: type uint16 LE (2B) + length uint16 LE (2B) + data (length bytes). First record must be BOF type 0x0809: version bytes at BOF+4 LE uint16 — 0x0600=BIFF8 (Excel 97-2003), 0x0500=BIFF5 (Excel 5/95). Stream offset = (firstDirSector+1) × 512. Macros in 'VBA' stream (inside storage named 'Macros' or '_VBA_PROJECT_CUR'). XLM/Excel 4.0 macros in dedicated 'Macro' sheets in Workbook stream BoundSheet records with hidden=2. Tools: oletools, xlrd, python-xlrd.",
    "Confirm OLE2 magic D0 CF 11 E0 A1 B1 1A E1",
    "Find 'Workbook' stream in CFB directory; first 4B = BOF record (type=0x0809, length follows)",
    "Check BOF version at Workbook+4: 0x0600 = BIFF8 (Excel 97-2003)",
    "Scan for 'VBA'/'_VBA_PROJECT_CUR' storage in CFB directory (macro indicator)",
    "Search BoundSheet8 records (type=0x0085) — hidden=2 in bit 1-4 of grbit field indicates hidden macro sheet",
    "Look for DDEAUTO formula patterns in FORMULA/LABELSST records (formula starting with '=')",
    "The Workbook stream contains sequential BIFF8 records — each record starts with type(2)+len(2)+data.",
    "XLM macro sheets (BIFF Macro type records) are a common malware vector predating VBA.",
    "VBA macros in the vbaProject storage are also a high-risk vector.",
    "EXTERNNAME records reference external named ranges used in DDE injection attacks.",
    "MULRK records efficiently encode multiple numeric cells in a compressed format.",
    "Shared formula records (SHRFMLA) optimize repeated formula storage across rows."
  ],
  "software": [
    "Microsoft Excel 97-2003",
    "LibreOffice Calc",
    "Apache OpenOffice Calc",
    "Google Sheets (import)",
    "oletools (forensic)"
  ],
